<br><a href="https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.3109/01443615.2014.958449?journalCode=ijog20" target="_self" style="color: rgb(222, 171, 91);">A 2013 study</a> measured the impact of rose oil on menstrual cramps. Women who experienced menstrual pain were given abdominal massages with diluted rose essential oil. The women massaged with rose oil reported less pain following the massage than the placebo group, demonstrating the powerful effect of rose oil. <br>
<br><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4387651/" target="_self" style="color: rgb(222, 171, 91);">A study in 2015</a> looked at the effects of inhaling rose essential oil after surgery in children. The children who inhaled the aroma of rose oil reported a significant decrease in their pain levels. Researchers believe that inhaling rose oil may have stimulated the release of endorphins – our body’s natural pain killer. <br></span></p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0473/9999/3493/t/3/assets/pf-346950c5--Massage-hands_500x.jpg?v=1606852168" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0473/9999/3493/t/3/assets/pf-346950c5--Massage-hands.jpg?v=1606852168 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0473/9999/3493/t/3/assets/pf-346950c5--Massage-hands_500x.jpg?v=1606852168 320w" width="640" height="427" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-cZMNgc fhouYJ pf-227_"/></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fHeRUh ixLxDV pf-228_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-evcjhq leJfDA"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-229_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-230_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-231_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-232_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-233_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-234_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-bTfYFJ iRKxGS pf-235_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-237_">How to use essential oils for pain relief<br></span></h3><p class="sc-uojGG ctGoIP pf-238_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-240_">How you decide to use essential oils for pain relief will depend on the type of pain you’re experiencing, as well as your personal preferences. Here are some of our favourite ways to use essential oils for pain relief.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-241_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-bTfYFJ iRKxGS pf-242_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-244_">Aromatherapy massage for pain relief<br></span></h3><p class="sc-uojGG ctGoIP pf-245_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-247_">An aromatherapy massage is a great way to soothe aching or sore muscles and to alleviate pain. You can ask a partner or friend to massage you, visit a qualified masseuse or have a go at self-massage. <br>
<br>It’s important to never apply essential oils undiluted or neat to your skin as they may cause skin irritation. Instead, mix a few drops of essential oil with a tablespoon of carrier oil such as coconut oil or jojoba oil. The mixture can then be massaged into your skin for you to enjoy the analgesic effects of your chosen essential oil.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-248_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-bTfYFJ iRKxGS pf-249_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-251_">Inhaling essential oils for pain relief<br></span></h3><p class="sc-uojGG ctGoIP pf-252_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-254_">Inhaling essential oils is an effective method of pain relief whilst also making your home smell delicious. Simply add a few drops of your chosen essential oil to an aromatherapy diffuser and inhale the aroma. <br>
<br>If you don’t own a diffuser, you can add a couple drops of essential oil to the hot wax of a lit candle to create your own personal scented candle. You can also try adding bergamot oil into a bowl of hot water and inhale the steam. It may seem strange that just inhaling essential oils could help reduce pain, but remember that our smell receptors are closely linked to the limbic system, the part of the brain responsible for emotions and for controlling the stress response, including breathing, heart rate and blood pressure. So it should come as no surprise that simply smelling the aroma of essential oils can have such powerful effects on the body.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-255_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-bTfYFJ iRKxGS pf-256_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-258_">Aromatherapy bath for pain relief<br></span></h3><p class="sc-uojGG ctGoIP pf-259_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-261_">A warm bath can have huge benefits if you’re suffering from pain. Hydrotherapy is an effective method of pain relief in itself, especially if your pain is muscular. The immersion, buoyancy and heat that come with a bath are a great way to alleviate pain whilst allowing your body to relax. <br>
<br>Couple this with pain-relieving essential oils to really reap the benefits of an aromatherapy bath. You’ll first need to mix your chosen essential oil with a tablespoon of carrier oil. This will help your oil to disperse effectively throughout the water, avoiding skin irritation. <br>
<br>If you don’t have any carrier oil on hand, don’t worry. You can also mix your chosen essential oil with a tablespoon of full-fat cow’s milk which will enable dispersion.<br></span></p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0473/9999/3493/t/3/assets/pf-7f9062db--Bath-diffuser_500x.jpg?v=1606845303" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0473/9999/3493/t/3/assets/pf-7f9062db--Bath-diffuser.jpg?v=1606845303 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0473/9999/3493/t/3/assets/pf-7f9062db--Bath-diffuser_500x.jpg?v=1606845303 320w" width="640" height="427" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-cZMNgc fhouYJ pf-262_"/></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fHeRUh ixLxDV pf-263_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-evcjhq leJfDA"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-264_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-265_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-266_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-267_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-268_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-269_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-270_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-271_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-bTfYFJ iRKxGS pf-272_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-274_">Is it safe to use essential oils for pain relief?<br></span></h3><p class="sc-uojGG ctGoIP pf-275_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-277_">Although essential oils are a natural product, there are a few safety guidelines you should follow when you’re practising aromatherapy. <br>
<br>As with anything, some people may experience an allergic reaction when using essential oils. If you’re applying essential oils to your skin, you should always mix them with a carrier oil first. This is because essential oils are extremely potent and can cause skin irritation if applied undiluted. It’s also important to do a patch test to check for skin irritation before using the oil more liberally. <br>
<br>Should you experience any symptoms of an allergic reaction, you should stop using the essential oil immediately, rinse any oil from your skin and contact your medical provider for advice. <br>
<br>If you are pregnant, breastfeeding or have a health condition, you should always consult your medical provider before using essential oils, as certain oils may not be compatible with certain health conditions. 
